original: Hultstrand, Arne Natanael, komminister, Skede, f. 12/12/09’ i Härlunda, Kronob. 1., av kantorn o. folkskrlär. Vdktor H. o. Hilda Ohlsson. — Stud:-ex. i Lund 28, teol. fil. ex. där 29, teol. kand., prakt. teol. prov samt prästv. f. Växjö stift 32. Tjg. s. pastiadj. i Korsberga o. Kalvsvik, v. pastor i Fli-seryd, pastradj. o. v. kommin. i Sofia förs. i Jönköp. samt v. kommin. i Vetlanda, kommin. i Skede sed. 36, pred. v. Ryhovs sjukh. i Jönköp. 35. Ordf. i folksk :styr., kyrkostämma, barnavind, fam:bidr:nd, biblistyr. samt i styr. f. Skede barnhem, led. av styr. f. S. K. K. i Jöniköp. 1. o. Coreniifonden Skr.: Skede förs. krönika (37), art. i tidn. o. tidskr.
translated: Hultstrand, Arne Natanael, Minister, Skede, born December 12, 1909 in Härlunda, Kronob. 1., son of a cantor and a primary school teacher, Viktor H. and Hilda Ohlsson. He obtained his Studentexamen (university entrance qualification) in Lund in 1928, followed by a degree in theology in 1929, and a theological candidate degree, practical theology exam, and ordination for Växjö diocese in 1932. He served as Deputy Pastor in Korsberga and Kalvsvik, Assistant Pastor in Fliseryd, Curate and Assistant Minister in Sofia parish in Jönköping, and Assistant Minister in Vetlanda before becoming a Minister in Skede in 1936. He was a preacher at Ryhov Hospital in Jönköping in 1935. He served as Chairman of the primary school board, church council, child welfare, family welfare, biblical committee, and Skede orphanage board, and was a member of the Swedish Christian Council in Jönköping and the Corenius Foundation. He wrote the Skede parish chronicle (1937) and articles in newspapers and magazines. He got married in 19XX.
